# Kora — environment variables for Vercel + Supabase
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` for local development.
# For Vercel, set the same variables in:
#   Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#
# Required variables are marked REQUIRED below. Without them, the app will
# hard-fail at build time (production) or render demo data (dev).

# ============================================================
# REQUIRED
# ============================================================

# Supabase project URL — public.
# Find it at https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/_/settings/api

# Supabase anon (publishable) key — public. RLS is the security boundary.
# Find it at the same dashboard page, marked "anon public".

# ============================================================
# OPTIONAL
# ============================================================

# Public site origin — used for redirect URLs and share OG metadata.
# Defaults to https://kora.studio if unset.
# Example for local dev:  NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# SERVER-ONLY — Supabase service-role key for elevated operations
# (storage uploads, AI admin paths, migration tooling).
# NEVER expose this to a client component. NEVER prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_.
# Find it at https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/_/settings/api
# (marked "service_role" — keep secret).

# SERVER-ONLY — OpenAI key for the real provider implementation.
# Without it, the AI provider falls back to a deterministic stub that
# returns seeded suggestions without consuming model tokens.
# Get one at https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
